OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1778746038
OL,3,CWhite-tailed eagles to be released on
OL,4,CExmoor to boost numbers in the wild
OL,6,FWatch: White-tailed eagles are
OL,7,Fflourishing on the Isle of Wight where
OL,8,Fthey have already been released.
OL,10,FWhite-tailed eagles, Britain's largest
OL,11,Fbird of prey, are set to return to the
OL,12,Fskies over Exmoor, in a bid to boost
OL,13,Fthe species' numbers in the wild.
OL,15,FThe release of up to 20 young eagles
OL,16,Fover the course of three years follows
OL,17,Fapproval for the scheme by Natural
OL,18,FEngland.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/12
